rComments: The lecture content is very interesting, he knows how to grab attention, however, he expects more than he gives. I took two classes with him and they were very interesting, but i really wish he will go more in depth in his teaching, it seems like he doesnt put as much effort. BUT again he is great in making you get interested in topic.

Write down everything he says in lecture and study it all. The crazy amounts of readings he assigns are so useless in my opinion, but if you're dying to do them, then just focus on the stuff he tells you to in lecture that's important. His exams are challenging, but if you go to office hours, he gives hints+ is very nice and funny.

rComments: I really enjoyed the material in lecture but that textbook was the worst thing I have ever read. It was extremely poorly written and the prof assigns a lot of unnecessary reading. That being said try to keep up with the reading with more focus on what he highlights in lecture, truly try to understand how it all works together to be successful.

rComments: He has great lecture slides that are easy to study off of and he explains everything really well. The class is at 9am but has WebOption so attendance isn't a big deal. There is only a midterm and final worth 40% & 60% respectively and are hard if you cram last minute or don't put in too much effort but he makes the material easy to understand.

basically paid $600 to read a book. You're better off watching youtube videos to learn concepts. He is new, and you can tell - too much "ahh" "umm" during lectures. Flips back and forth with analogies when trying to explain a topic. Exams were based on the material required, but it was evident he was trying to maintain a low class average.  Avoid.

He explains things quite well in his lectures. The textbook readings can get a little time consuming, but if you prioritize relevant sections in the textbook, you can do well in the course. The exams are fair in my opinion; I actually studied only for 2 days (that includes doing the readings and textbook questions) for the final and got 95 overall.

His tests are very hard and the lectures are a waste of time. Everything on the exams are from the textbook readings which are EXTREMELY long. He's also not the most helpful prof so you're kinda on your own when learning this course.

Read the assigned readings for the textbook. All of it. There are no tricks, just a significant amount of readings. Definitely go to office hours, he's a pretty chill guy with a sense of humour. He will make sure to answer your questions fully if you make the effort to ask for help.

Super funny prof. Lectures are short concise but are more of the entertainment portion of the class. FOCUS ON THE TEXTBOOK! Exams are super difficult. All application based and super detailed. Not a course to procrastinate with. Read every single detail in the text book and see if you can apply concepts to the real world.
